  <refnamediv>
    <refname>RPI_gertboardAnalogRead</refname>
    <refpurpose>Function to read voltage from gertboard</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>


<refsynopsisdiv>
   <title>Calling Sequence</title>
   <synopsis>
   RPI_gertboardAnalogRead(pin)
   
   </synopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv>

<refsection>
   <title>Parameters</title>
   <variablelist>
   <varlistentry><term>pin:</term>
      <listitem><para>the pin to read the voltage from. Numbering follows the pinBase from RPI_gertboardSetup function.</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   </variablelist>
</refsection>

<refsection>
   <title>Description</title>
   <para>
After initialinzing the pinBase using the RPI_gertboeardSetup function, reading channel pinBase + 0 reads the first analog input channel (pin DA0 on the Gertboard). Returns a value from 0 to 1023 representing the value on the supplied pin.
   </para>
   <para>
</para>
</refsection>

<refsection>
   <title>Examples</title>
   <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
RPI_gertboardAnalogRead(101)
   ]]></programlisting>
</refsection>

